Chapter One: The Apocalypse
 
     Thera, the land of our birth, the aira that we breathe, the food,
water, all friends and things you know, are but remnants of a 
world long dead.  You are the children this world's fate depends 
on. You are the sole survivors of a once rich world, where 
technology and magic were meshed together in unity.  You are 
the children of a new dawn. I write this short history for all to 
know, learn and understand. Do not let this knowledge slip away 
from your hands less you repeat the same mistakes (as many 
have already done) that your ancestors did. After you have read 
this document, I pray you will see the world with a new vision, 
as a child wakes up to a new reality each day. All the things you 
thought you knew were passed on by generations of ignorance 
let me deliver your soul with some badly needed answers. I 
sometimes think that as I grow older (as we all do...) we are 
nothing more than misinformed children, running free in a 
garden of death. We are born with many questions, and so little 
answers, let me shed some light on your past ... at least for a little 
while...
 
     I shall try to explain first the nature of magic, as you know it today,
and in the past. I shall then continue with a close look at what 
technology did to us, and will explain the nature of our planet disaster. 
Magic, as we call it today, is a part of everything we do in our time ... 
and we use rituals, prayers, articles and many more to accomplish our 
magic might.  In the olds days, mages, or any spellcaster for that matter, 
did not exit, their names were "psychics" or "mystics", and they drew 
their powers from their minds and souls. They were masters of the 
body and mind, and could communicate as a whole network
of minds. They could go without substance for days on end, and gather 
up their will to transform their bodies in animal essences and become 
the animals they would reflect in their minds (it is believe that druids 
still withhold the secrets of this transformation, but this is mere 
speculation). We have no other type of spellcaster alive today that are 
equal in power to the Naturalist ...  as they were called.  
 
     The only possible exception would be the guild of "Prodigy" which 
focuses mental energies with meditation, a bit like the naturalist, but 
they are eons away yet in their final evolution to the previous state of 
perfection attained by the Naturalist. We all posses magical abilities 
today, much because it is genetic, and we have evolved to this state, but 
we need specific guild lines to focus our wills, for example; the mage 
need to recite words and gestures, the alchemist needs to concoct 
potions and brews, the prodigist need his meditative trances, the cleric 
prays in fervent belief to his god (I do not mean offense ... if there are 
gods that walk the realm, I do not think any know for sure the answer, 
but it is certain that clerics derive their spell from the intensity of the 
prayers ... and their Belief in their god), the necromancer goes through 
his rituals of death and as for the rest, well. I will be glad to speak 
further of it, but in future notes. 
 
     As for the Industrialist, those who wield technology and make all 
the rest sway to its powers. Well, let me give you an example of what 
technology was at the time. Imagine taking the top 10 buildings in 
Midgaard, and place walkways from one to the other ... people could 
come and go, free of the traffic and crowds below them. Now, imagine 
making each building in your city about 200 to 300 feet high, and some 
even up to 500 feet, and making walkways and bridges each 30 feet or 
so, and imagine a road build from on end of town to the other end, with
nothing but empty air below... and imagine it going to the next city, and 
the next and the next, and beyond.
 
     Humans at the time thought big, really BIG. They were not 
satisfied with any of their environments and set off to change the very 
nature of Nature, with gene splicing. Thus, the G.E.F.N.O.S. experiment 
was born. Gefnos stands for genetically experience for new organic 
status.  Humans were not satisfied as a whole about the slow evolution 
of man, people were still dying of old age, and people wanted a cure;
for cancer. Quick, and soon. Not every one was born a mystic, and so 
people wanted results. The project goal was to successfully augment 
humans using genesplicer technology, and with it, eliminate all flaws 
from the human body. The project was at an experimental state, and 
was only used on animals and ... later, bacteria (mainly to see where 
and how we could change its genetic Nature ... even in such a primitive 
form). They built a whole complex, as big as a district, and in it were 
twelve nuclear reactors.  Its days would end with disaster... and mans 
kind with it.
 
     Naturalist believes that technology is to be used by humans, yes, 
this they agreed. But they completely disagree with the notion that 
technology should be used to alter the human state, body, and soul ... it 
was an insult to their face. They, at first, objected to the experiment, 
and soon protested openly against it, rallying thousands to their 
demonstrations. The industrialized government would hear none of it ... 
they wanted Supreme Being for their own.
 
