0 'HORDE'~
The horde of Kentari originated from the Kentari Plateaus of
eastern Thera.  Although considered barbarians by most people, they
are actually a group of highly superstitious hunters and gatherers. 
They are known to hate magic and anything resulting from magic.  They
avoid cities and civilization because that is where magic seems to be
strongest.  The horde consists of mainly warriors, thieves,
mercenaries, and any warrior-type classes that are willing to abandon
their magical skills (I.  E.  Black Knights, assassins, rangers and
paladins.)  Bards does not use real magic, but tricks of the eye and
they provide a good source of entertainment and folklore to the
population.  All other classes are shunned by the horde because of
their weak body.  The horde recruits races of moderate to great
strength.  They especially value giants, trolls, and ogres.  They
value felars, gargoyles, and human for their speed and dwarves and
dreugers for their endurance.  They detest pixies, elves, birdmen,
and the other weaker and smaller-sized races.  The horde believes
that enduring a hard life will bring strength and endurance to body
and soul.  They seem to have developed some forms of resistance to
magic because of this and are very tough warriors.  They believe that
the gods are almighty and they are living under the laws of god. 
They answer to only one set of law and that is of the gods.  The god
of power provides the strength for them to endure the hard life.  The
god of death provides them with the release of life and pain.  The
goddess of Life and goddess of creation grant them the power to grow.
Although they do acknowledge the existence of the god of magic, they
do not worship him.  The horde has quite a few seemingly strange
rituals.  One is that they believe that wearing the skin of their
fallen victims will give them power and courage in battle.  Another
would be that they will only loot the non-magical items of their
victims and will sacrifice the rest to their gods.  The origin of the
Horde was a humble and tragic one.  The horde's original ancestors
were decimated by a lone evil mage.  The chieftain at the time did
battle with him, but lost.  The evil mage's powerful fireballs
incinerated him and what is left of the chieftain is his Iron Skull. 
The skull has become the Horde's artifact and source of pride and
encouragement in the face of magic.  Their hatred for magic does not
end there.  They believe that magic and the search for magic caused
the Great Apocalypse so going back to the gods and the basics of life
is what the gods had intended.  Magic and knowledge disrupts their
belief system and they will adamantly fight them if they have to. 
The pass leaders of the Hordes usually either ignore the mages
completely and lived a peaceful life with god and nature or they
fought the mages furiously.  They rarely ever allied with magical
beings and only do so in the worst of times.  
 
For more information type:
Kingdom info Horde
