0 'KUJIKIRI'~
The true history of Kujikiri, before they came to Thera, is known
only to their leaders. That is a story that is passed from Shihan to
Shihan. What is known, however, is Kujikiri's history in Thera, which
began the moment their ships hit the beach...
 
     Their great ships hit Thera's beaches in the month of the Hawk, day
of the Sun. The great dark ships landed, surprising the local residents,
as the ships seemed to sneak into the harbor. The people of these ships
were dark of skin, and their clothes were strange. They said they were
called 'Kujikiri'. Yet they also made their leader distinguished in
garb. Cloaked in dark purple silks, and silver trinkets, his name
was Shihan Dainyo.
 
     Now, these were the days of Valiss, and thusly, these strangers-
from-the-sea were taken to him. Dainyo had made some efforts to learn
to speak Thera's common language, and soon after meeting Valiss, Kujikiri
began trading their odd goods and knowledge. It was not long after this
first meeting that Kujikiri settled in to Thera.
 
     However, these people of Kujikiri were albeit introverted, which
made these people seem rather mysterious to the other people of Thera,
and out of this mystery many rumors were born. Moreover, the people
of Kujikiri did things in strange ways, they spoke differently, faught
differently, their magic was completely foreign to the ways of Thereans
usually performed their magic, and more importantly, these people of
Kujikiri seemed to be masters of the night. It was this that bore the
title: The Shadows of Kujikiri. This nickname was embraced by the people
of Kujikiri, meaning something different to them than what it obviously
meant to the Thereans. These things confused the people of Thera, and
soon, many people begun to believe that Kujikiri were an evil people.
 
     Evil, however, they were not. The people of Kujikiri have a strong
sense of 'Face', their own unique brand of honor. They are deadly
loyal to their friends, and enemies are treated with either strict
ruthlessness, or mocking playfullness, depending of course on the enemy.
In addition to their love of secrecy, these qualities led people to
begin to fear Kujikiri, branding them 'Dark', and 'Evil'. This, however,
is a false image, Kujikiri is somewhat of an isolationist nation when
it comes to the affairs of other nations, more neutral in these matters
than anyone else.
 
 
For more information on Kujikiri type:
Kingdom info Kujikiri
change Kingdom info Kujikiri
