0 'AUCTION'~
Syntax: auction <item>
Syntax: auction
Syntax: auction bet <amount gold>
Syntax: auction <on/off>
 
An auction system exists in Fate, which allows players to auction off items to
the highest bidder.  The auction is worldwide, allowing you to bid from
anywhere within the reaches of Thera.
 
To auction off an item, you simply type "auction <item>", the item will then be
placed on the bidding table.  
 
Once an item is auctioned, you receive a chance to bet on the item, the command
being "auction bet <amount of gold>".  After placing your bet, other players
will be given 2 chances to bid.  After one tick, the item will go once.  After
another  tick, the item will be going twice.  And after a third tick, the item
will be sold to the player holding the current bet.  Each time a new bet is
placed, the chances will be reset, allowing you two more chances to place a
higher bet.
 
You can check the stats and info of the item being auctioned, using the command
"auction"
 
There are a number of tricks to ease the betting process:
 
"auction bet x <number>" will multiply the current bet by a value, the default
being 2. 
 
"auction bet + <percent>" will bet a certain percent higher than the previous
bet, the default geing 25%.  Advanced strings are also accepted.
 
"auction bet 14k" is the equivalent of betting 14,000 gold.
~

