1 ool~
The OOL (Out-Of-Level) Rule can be described as a combination of
various rules, involving your assistance and/or interference to characters
outside of your PK range.
 
The following is a list of actions that are considered unnacceptable
under OOL:
 
- Powerleveling someone that is out of your PK range.
- Spelling up or healing an individual while they are in the midst of a PK
      - This means they are unable to quit due to "having too much fun
            right now."
- Leading aggie mobs to someone out of your PK range in order to kill
      a character.
- Looting the corpse of someone outside of your PK range.
      - The only exception to this if you're looting in order to return the
         character's eq, and this may only be done if the character died
         from a non-PK related death.
- Killing a character's charmie/pets when the character is outside of your
      PK range. This also includes using blindness dust to blind charmies/pets
      of someone.
 
The following is a list of actions that are considered acceptable under OOL:
 
- Looting the corpse of someone outside of your PK range, if their death
      is non-PK related, and you have their permission.
- Spelling up an individual *BEFORE* a PK starts.
- Portalling someone who is OOL, to a target within their PK range.
 
Punishment for breaking the OOL rule can vary and sometimes result in a slay of
the offending character.
~

