For the time being, there will be no formal, coded religion
system for Fate of Kingdoms.  There are hopes and plans to implement
one at some point in the future.
 
RP Guide: Roleplaying religion is, however, strongly encouraged - particulary
for clerics.  A good roleplay model should be based on the assumed
"facts" of life on Thera.  We will asume a pervasive religious system
which honors Takeda as a nearly all powerful god who conquered wild
elemental forces early in the Age.
    Takeda's goals are often clouded, but those of his servants,
the other main gods, are not.  Their charateristics are widely
known and they interact with mortals on a fairly frequent basis.
Those that worship these gods are seen as devote on Thera.
    It should be noted that many of the devote still distrust or
hate the druids.  Many years ago, a group of druids tried to release
a powerful elemental spirit and destroy the gods.  They were stopped,
but only after great bloodshead and sorrow.  Non-druids who worship
gods other than these, are considered to be lunatics.
 
For more information on what the god each administrator roleplays
stands for, enter help [Admin's name]
~

