0 riannon~
My Father, Larnth was a high rank demon worshipper for the former
mighty Kingdom of Narssius.  He spent many years worshipping Zelphax
and informing other of his being.  Because of great devotion to his
kingdom he was a huge part of the war that came upon.  The war
between Gondor and Narssius.  Because of Larnth's great involvement
in the war and the dangerous environment that Larnth's wife was in
she fled out of reach from the war.  Anthra, my mother, ended up at a
sea shore hungry, cold, and confused.  Lonely night after lonely
night passed by while she sat on the shore crying, when a slightly
familiar face appeared and began to comfort her.  She couldn't
remember where or how she knew this person, maybe it was all in
imagination.  Xarnix restored her faith in life and nursed her back
to health.  They spent many nights together inside his cave near the
sea shore until he talked her into returning back to Thera to stand
proud beside her husband's side.  She found herself, yet again, alone
when she reached the town of Sanaria.  Larnth had been killed in the
war.  Anthra searched all over for the person responsible for the
death of her husband, but was not successful.  Having no idea what to
do or how she was going to survive.  Anthra became numb.  She sat in
her cottage, that was right outside the town of Sanaria, day in and
day out for a long while, completely saddened.  During the long time
that she spent locked up inside her cottage she gave birth to me. 
Still in the state of depression Anthra didn't take very good care of
me.  I laid on the dirt floor of our cottage for the eight days
straight, after my birth.  She was only acknowledging my presence
when I was hungry.  I was told that a man was passing by the cabin
and heard the desperate cries of an infant, so he entered the cabin. 
When he entered he found me cold, hungry, and on my last breathe.  He
seized me from the horrible place, taking me from my mother.  That is
all that has been told to me of my past.  What I can remember of my
childhood is sitting next to a large tree watching the grass blow in
the wind and sometimes going into New Thalos to talk to the
townspeople.  At the end of the day I would return to a small one
room shack in the woods.  This shack had only a cot and a table with
one chair.  Each night when I'd return from my days journey I'd find
a hot plate of food.  Each morning when I awoke I'd find a hot plate
of food.  I always assumed that it was this, that rescued me from my
mother, giving me this food.  But I was never sure, for I never seen
him or her or whatever it was that was feeding me.  When I out grew
my belongings I'd find more on my cot when I returned at the end of
the day.  I found this very odd but I was thankful for whoever it was
that was feeding me.  I stayed in that one room shack till I felt as
if I were ready to go out on my own.  On my own I realized that I was
unwanted/unaccepted by the townspeople.  They taunted and teased me
to no end.  A feeling of total rejection I couldn't take it.  I
couldn't bare another moment of the abuse.  So I left.  During my
many travels alone I came across numerous amounts of different
people.  Having no food, no possessions, and no water I began to
steal to survive.  I found that looting solved all my problems.  Life
for me continued this way until the day I came across a man named
Conrad who showed me the error of my ways.  He put hope in my heart
and order in my life.  Setteling in Sanaria I began to make friends. 
I never forgot what I had been through.  Also I always asked new
people that I met if that had known or heard stories of my parents. 
The only thing that I was told by more than one person, which I
assume to be true, was that he died on the day of the sun.  Because I
had spent so much time gone from here most that were around during
the time of the Gondor Narssius war were now passed.  Even the
kingdom Narssius is now gone.  One day sitting at the Center Square
in Sanaria thinking back on my childhood a pair of feet stood infront
of me and dropped something at my feet.  I turned to ask his name but
he was already gone.  When I looked back at my feet I seen a book. 
As I picked it up I realized it was a journal.  The front of the
journal had the Narssiuss Symbol on it and it had written on ink at
the bottom skip every other one, but don't start with the first -
start at the second.  Extremely nervous to find out what was inside I
opened it.  To my disappointment the journal was in bad shape.  Every
page of the journal had a burn over certain sentences, words, or
phrases.  I've tried to figure out what the missing words on the
pages wrote, but I've been unsuccessful.  The only thing I know is
that this is my fathers journal and it could possible lead to who
killed him.  The last journal entry is marked the day of the sun,
