0 nyxx~
Eons ago the illithid race massed in a dimension unknown to the
theran population. The illithids were quite aware of their weak
other-dimensional neighbours, and as the illithids evolved they
learned to master the art of travelling across the boundaries of the
two dimensions.
The far more intelligent and evolved illithids wrecked havoc on the still 
infant human civilization, and brought back thousands of slaves to their
own dimension. Over the years the slaves themselves evolved to fit their 
new harsh enviroment and thus spawned the darnok race...
 
As generations passed even the illithid community became familiar with 
lack of discipline, and slowly renegades and criminals began to surface 
amongst the illithids. Still maintaining control.
The High Emperor Khurnazphorr II ordered his most trusted advisors to 
think up an effective way to punish these unwanted subjects in a way that 
would not be an economical burden to the Empire.
The advisors did their job well...
 
A desolate dimension was located, and it was named Nyxx. The 
interdimensional pathfinders created an oneway portal leading to Nyxx. A 
prison dimension had been created.
The High Emperor was pleased with the solution, and began deporting 
unwanted elements there
Immediately. While civil unrest still lingered among the illithids, the 
darnok slaves had also begun to cause trouble. Having lost their human 
weaknesses, their mental prowess had developed until it reached a 
frightening degree. Rebellions broke out more and more often in the slave 
camps, and the Emperor found it necessary to deport the darnoks who 
were too dangerous to keep around the dimension, alongside those 
impossible to enslave or force to work.
Thus the population on Nyxx grew both in numbers and in race variety...
Having already concluded that Nyxx held no values, and hardly the natural 
resources to sustain life for a vast amount of people, The Emperor and his 
advisors saw no need to keep a watch on Nyxx. They knew the 
interdimensional portal could only be used one way, and therefore  
considered the problem solved. 
As time passed the banished illithid renegades and criminals found 
themselves forced to try and co-exist with their former darnok slaves. The 
harsh dimension they had been forced into exile within simply demanded 
cooperation if anyone was to survive. Slowly they learned to harness each 
others strengths and make up for each others weaknesses, and a new 
multiracial community was created in the prison dimension of Nyxx.
For several generations the inhabitants of Nyxx could do nothing but fight 
to survive. The struggle to harness the few natural resources available, the 
struggle against famine, the constant battle to fight off assaults from vile 
creatures and terrible storms of unbelievable strength all aided both in 
strengthening the bond between the two races, but also to empower the 
individuals over generations of evolution.
 
As time passed their community became so well established that they 
could begin to focus on other more important things, such as how to 
escape...?
The brightest minds of Nyxx no matter the race were gathered in a council 
that had the sole purpose of working on a way to escape their prison 
world. Much of the knowledge of dimensional travelling had been lost 
over time, and progress was slow for the council. 
The seats in the council were given from parent to child alongside any 
knowledge they had gained, and for countless years many generations 
worked towards the very same goal. Slowly but steadily their knowledge 
of the travelling magic was learned once more. At first only working 
within the dimension as they could not yet uphold a portal for more than 
seconds, but later their skill and power grew and they soon mastered the 
pathways known as nexus. 
Now they turned their eyes away from Nyxx, searching outwards towards 
other worlds. Only myths had survived of the known dimensions visited 
eons ago, and their search was made in blindness, as they had no clue 
where to seek a suitable dimension to seize as their new home. The vague 
recollection of a realm known as Thera still lingered in the memory of the
darnoks, as the tale had been passed down all the way from their human 
ancestors. 
~

