0 ARRUDOR~
In the beginning of the world when Thera was first formed, there
lived an ancient, powerful group of people called the Arrudor.
The reason for their power was such that they understood that
nature and magic are essentially the same thing of origin, and
there are no differences between the two. They understood that
the power of nature and the other mystical magic power cannot
exist without the other. They enjoyed wielding their power and
shaped the world as they saw fit. They lived in this utopia for
many generations.
 
Sadly, after many eons have passed, the younger generation of this
ancient race had forgotten the source of their power. They had
forgotten the importance of the co-existance between nature and
magic. The younger generations broke into two different sects, a
group of people studying in the power of nature, these people later
became druids, rangers and such. The other sect of people studied
in the magical powers, they later became wizards and prodigies.
Althought the two sects lived in harmony at first, this harmony
between them did not last for long as they disagree with each other
on many subjects. Fearing that a civil war might occur and that
the newborns will forget the true source of their powers, the elders
wrote down all their knowledges and instilled it into the tome of
magic. They sealed it such that only the God knows where it can be
found.  As the elders expected, a civil war broke out. This ancient 
race of people destroyed their own kin without mercy. In their history 
this was called "Proelium ab Natura Magus". It wiped out almost all 
of their populations, those who survived are forgotten in time. They
took form of other newborn races and forgot about their roots.
 
Sesori, without knowing it himself, was one of such desendent. The
Rogue diety Drenalus, seeing how it would be useful to have such
power to be have by himself, Drenalus called out to Sesori. Knowing
that only the desendent of the once powerful race can wield wuch
power, Drenalus hoped that the drow will listen to his every wishes
in the future, from such, Drenalus told Sesori about the ancient
tome of magic and sent Sesori on the quest to seek out the tome. Not
knowing Drenalus' true intention and curious about such ultimate
power. The young drow set out to the quest.
 
However, Drenalus' plan did not succeed. As Mahongeon, the God of
nature and magic saw through his plan and drove him away. Mahongeon,
feeling sorry for the drow, sent down his avatar and to the drow
and presented to him the tome he had been searching for. After
reading the tome his ancestor had wrote about the ancient power,
Sesori knows what must be done. He must start a kingdom and help
those of the other descendents remember their true identify. 
Together, they will bring back the old power they once had.
 
SEE ALSO:  ARRUDOR2
~

