0 DEATH~
When you die, you are reincarnated  in your hometown. Your corpse is
left behind where you died. Consider yourself lucky to find any of your
gear left in it. Being reincarnated is no minor deal. Every third death
results in the loss of a random stat.  However you lost con more often
than any other stats. Eventually you will have a constitution that is too 
low to render reincarnation. It is at that final point that you will NEVER 
again see life. You die for good!  So take care, it may be closer than 
you think...But then again most people do not seem to worry about it 
or even see it happen.
 
What people DO see however, are haunting spirits...
When you die, the spirits of all those players you have killed
come back to do various things to you. The more the merrier.
These spirits will wait for your spirit to be released always and
they can cause great trauma in large enough numbers. Nothing a hardy
adventurer could not recover from though. Also, some gods have
been known to destroy the haunting spirits,... for a good reason
 
You do NOT lose constitution or even experience from raw kills
where you have not a fighting chance...i.e. one hit wonders.
 
Any spells which were affecting you are canceled by death.
Following and groups are not affected by death.
 
You lose experience points for dying.  The amount you lose depends on 
your then experience points, your race, class and your previous deaths.
 
Corpses decay after time, but the objects inside corpses fall to the ground.
~

