stubbornness.  Dwarves are not taken to flights of fancy, but neither are
they totally grim and humorless.  Family history, clan and personal honor
are of utmost importance to the dwarven race.  They take their duties
seriously, be they a warrior, guardsman, clergy, or merchant.  Dwarves
