0 SERRATOR~
The kingdom known as Serrator began, when a young elven monk
by the name of Tharn had a vision.  He was the last elven monk
to ever live in Thera, as the guild had been forgotten among elves.
One day, while he was sleeping at an inn in Sanaria, he had a dream.
An angel send by the goddess of justice, Riannon, commanded him
to start a divine kingdom, following the will of the gods, and
bringing justice to all.  Tharn then began his search for people
who would believe in his vision and follow him.  The first one he
found was an Illithid by the name of Swirhun.  Tharn told him of
his vision, and he eagerly followed.  These two spread the word about
Thera, and soon a giant named Galberoth and a darnok named Niadh
decided to follow him.  The kingdom was ready to start.  Tharn
taught his followers how to pray, and worship, and all Serrator
members must.  Because Serrator is a kingdom of the divine, dark
magics are not widely used.  Therefore, dark-magic users may not
advance past rank 6, along with non-magic users.  Serrator is
divided into 4 sections, the heads of each form a council that
runs the kingdom.  This comes from a tradition that monks of
the Ivory Temple practice.  These 4 groups are called robes.
the first, and lowest group, consisting of ranks 1-3 is the red
robe, its leader being the Paige.  The next group is the yellow
robe, consisting of ranks 4-6, it's leader being the Seer.  The
next group is generally the most respected, it is the orange robe.
It consists of ranks 7-9, and all members of this robe are part of
the council.  The last group is the white robe.  The only person
in this group is the Cardinal, and leads the kingdom.  They head
the council.  All classes are accepted into Serrator, and may
advance by doing special things for the kingdom.
 
SEE ALSO:  SERRATOR2
~

0 SERRATOR2~
Serrator is a fairly peaceful kingdom, devoting
most of their time to worshipping the divine.
Members shall not kill without first consulting
the council of robes.  Serrator shall make treaties
with all who practice peaceful measures and are
willing to be a worth ally.  Members lower than rank
9 can be advanced in rank by doing things helpful
to the kingdom or things that bring the kingdom
honor and glory.  However, non-spellcasters and
non-magic users cannot advance past rank 6.
The ideal member for Serrator would be one that is
a spellcaster, of good or neutral background, such
as a cleric or monk and is prepared to worship
the divine.  People wishing to join the
conclave must be of at least level 20, and must
inform the robe council about their wish to
join.
~

0 BUGS~
A bug is defined as an error or mistake within the coding of the mud or the
building of an area, that gives you an unfair advantage over other players
of the MUD, or anything within the game, that common sense tells you,
shouldn't be occuring.
 
If you come across a bug, you should first pray, and see if an imm is currently
on, as an administrator can gain more information through a direct conversation
with you than he/she would by going through a note.
 
If you pray, and do not receive a response, then you should write a note to
'admin' on board 3, describing the bug and the events that lead up to it.
Here are a few things to keep in mind when writing the note:
 
- Describe exactly what you think is wrong.
- What items are in your inventory, what room you're in, what mobs are
      near you.
- Try not to get upset by the bug.  If there is a problem, we want the bug
      resolved just as much as you do.
 
Remember, the abuse of a bug, as well as the non-reporting of bugs, is
considered a very delicate matter by the Admin Staff, and both of the
afore-mentioned actions can lead to you receiving harsh treatment from
the Admin Staff.
 
Punishments for the abuse of a bug or failure to report a bug can be
severe as a slay.  If the bug abused changes information pertaining to
your character (changes stats, skills, spells, hp/mana, etc), special
punishment if deemed necessary may occur.
~

