    actions and beliefs.  It is also required that the reasons for
    which you are placing the bounty, must actually affect you in
    someway.  (Example:  Say Player A, murdered Player B.  If your
    RP involves being a murderous person, and you've no affiliation
    with Player B, then you cannot legitimately place the bounty,
    because in all reality, IC-wise, you would not care).
 
 
In order to accept bounties upon other characters, the following
requirements must be met:
 
1)  You must note admins, notifying them that your character accepts
    bounties (this need not apply to assassins).
 
2)  Your background, and previous rp, must be that which would support
    your character as being the type to accept bounties.  (Example:
    If your character was the leader of a peaceful kingdom, you would
    not be able to accept a bounty placed upon individual, due to
    morality issues and other IC beliefs, as your rp would not
    support it.)
 
3)  IC interaction with the person placing the bounty, must occur.
    It is also required that an IC note be written to you by the
    individual placing the bounty, that individual must note admins,
    and you too must note admins, informing the acceptance of the
    bounty that has been placed.
 
 
Essentially, lame bounty reasons placed on someone, so that you or your
friends may PK them freely, or simply because they have equipment you
desire to gain, *WILL NOT BE TOLERATED*.
 
PLEASE NOTE:  Players may still place bounties on board 2, but the requirements
still must be followed.
 
If you have any questions abount bounties, simply ask an admin, before
following through with the bounty.
 
SEE ALSO:  BOUNTYHUNTERS
~

0 PK~
The PK rule can be described as a combination of various rules involving
Player Killing, and is likely the most complex of rules in existance on Fate.
 
The following requirements must be met before a player can participate
in a PK:
 
- An appropriate background and description, as slated by their helpfiles.
- An IC reason/conflict between your character and the person you wish to attack.
      - The character stole from you, or a friend of yours.
      - The character is currently at war with your kingdom.
      - The character insulted you on isay or gossip, or antagonized you.
      - The character poses an IC threat to you (Their rp and actions hint that
            they may attack you - and use strong disgression here).
      - The character murdered you or a friend.
      - A bounty has been placed upon the individual. (see help bounty2)
      - Use common sense and good judgement.
 
If you and another character choose to duel, understand that both sides must
first agree, and also that duels are considered IC.  Please NOTE:
      - Treachery exists in Fate, and when participating in duels, you do
            so at your own risk.  The Admin Staff will not replace items lost
            in duels.
 
The following is *NOT* allowed during PK:
- OOL assistance (See: help OOL).
- PK'ing someone for an OOC reason.
- PK'ing someone your alt is at war with.
      - Read this as: If you die to someone on a char, you may not
            log on another alt in the same PK range in attempt to have
            your vengeance.
- PK'ing someone for leveling on a mob.
 
Following any PKs, a PK note is required to be written with 48
hours on board 6.  The note must contain both a OOC explanation,
and then an IC story of the events that occured leading up to the
death of your victim.
 
Punishment for breaking any of the PK rules can vary and severity,
and can result in a slay.  In very rare instances, a character will be
baled for excessive abuse of PK and ignoring the rules and regulations
set forth.  The Admin Staff understands that PK rules are very complex.
If you have any questions or concerns about a PK, simply ask an Admin
before following through with it.
~

