that gives a short explanation of your reason for the PK and
any other OOC notes.
 
(2) It must contain a longer in character section labeled IC:
that gives a detailed in-character account of the events from
your character's perspective.
 
PK notes are not optional and if you fail to write an accept-
able one, you may be punished for illegal PK.
~

0 "power leveling"~
Powerleveling is defined as excessive and continual aid from a highbie, while
an individual or group of lower-levels while leveling benefit from this.  An
example of this would be described as:
 
- A lvl 70 cleric, following around a group of lvl 30s, and continually healing
      the group, while deathfielding the mobs they are leveling on to make the
      mob easier to kill.
 
- A lvl 75 Maligner following a group, and repeatedly and excessively casting
      maledictions upon the mobs the group is leveling on.
 
Punishment for breaking the Power Leveling rule can result in punishment as
severe as a slay. In specific circumstances, punishment may be more severe
and less merciful, if for example, the power leveling was done by the player's
own alt, and then breaking both the Power Leveling and the Multi Playing rules.
~

