0 gaiastorm~
The Confederation of Gaiastorm began as a dream that formed in the
hearts of like minded mortals from many walks of life on Thera.  The
tale begins, however, in the Elven nation of Elrorian, on the night
of a terrible storm.  Building for days, the storm finally broke,
dumping a hellacious downpour of thunderously violent proportions
over the Elven city.  Finally, at the storm's climax, a mighty bolt
of lightning struck the ground.  When the rains settled, the Elves,
much to their shock, found that a small human boy sat in a puddle at
the base of their famous Tree of Restoration.  The boy, Elial, was
taken in by the Elven clerics and raised among the fair folk.  The
Elves believed that he was the fulfillment of a prophecy, a child who
would help bring about the restoration of the balance of Nature and
lead mortalkind to a greater understanding of the natural world.  The
Elves gave Elial the title of "He Who Rides the Storm."  His later
adventures would lead to his coming of age and Vision Quest, an
ancient tradition that determines the course of a young person's
life.  During this quest, he encountered the being that identified
itself as the Green Man, an entitiy apart from both Gods and mortals.
The Green Man gave Elial visions of others who had the intrinsic love
of nature in their hearts, and sent him to seek them out.  In time,
he did.  Thus was born the Confederation of Gaiastorm, named so in
honor of the storm that bore Elial to the Elves, and for the ferocity
with which the love of the natural world burns within the souls of
its memebers.  Gaiastorm is not a nation per say.  They are very
loosely bound to the Warder, who acts as a first among equals and
diplomat of sorts.  Nations who submit to cooperative Gaiastorm rule
gain the benefit of the knowledge of many who work with the land,
air, soil and water.  Gaiastorm also takes great pride in the
reclaimation of barren and destroyed land, making it suitable for
re-settlement and growth.  They can be somewhat militant if need
calls for it, though protecting the wilderness and serving the Green
Man as the Avatar of Nature will always come first, before
politicking and empire-building.  
 
For information on Gaiastorm's ranks, membership standards and code of
conduct, see 'HELP GAIASTORM2'
~

0 Gaiastorm2~
Additonal information on Gaiastorm and the
offical Code of Conduct:
 
Alignments allowed:  Gaiastorm is welcoming to
nearly all walks of life, with a philosophically
neutral viewpoint being the prevailant mode of
thinking.  Those of good moral standing will find
little problem fitting in as well.  It has nearly
always rang true, however, that evil beings do not
respect the land or life.  Excepting very highly rare
cases, evil will not be welcome.
 
 
Races allowed:  All, with the near-always exception
of the more fell monster races of Thera, namely orcs
and trolls.  These races have a long and profane history
of atrocities committed agains the Green.  The memories 
of the trees are very long.  If a member of these races
wishes to join our ranks, it must be for an extremely
good reason, and they must be highly trustworthy. 
Exceptions are rare.
 
 
Classes:  Again, nearly all are welcome, excepting
Black-Knights and Maligners.  Necromancers are a total
anathema of life, and will not be welcomed.
 
 
The Ranks of Confederacy are as follows:
 
10.  Warder - the leader of Gaiastorm.  A first among
equals.
9.  Divine - the Spiritual Advisor of the Warder, and
second-in-command.
8.  Stormguard - leaders of defense.  There shall be
at any point in time up to two for melee and two for
magical representation.
7.  Gnostic - scholars, keepers of the histories and lore
of Gaiastorm.
6.  Sentinel - the Elite Wilderness Defenders.
5.  Seeker - patrols the wilderlands.
4.  Preserver - aids in healing the land, and the restor-
ation of nature.
3.  Woodsman/mistress - the caretakers of the wilds, both
flora and fauna.
2.  Medicine Man/Woman - learns more of ancient lore, craft
and traditions of Gaiastorm.
1.  Scout - initiate level, a student of the Confederacy.
 
Those interested in joining the Confederacy should first
look into their hearts and see if they meet the qualifications.
You should then make your intentions known to the Warder, and
then to the world by public delcaration (RP board).  We will
then let you know.
~

