The following abilities are the inherent racial skills of the player-character
races on Fate of Kingdoms.
 
Illithid - "Paralysis" SYNTAX:  paralysis <victim>
An illithid has a chance of paralyzing a victim with their mind powers.  It works
much like the spell ESP.
 
Pixie - "flitter".  This is an AUTOMATIC skill that allows the pixie to get in
extra dodges due to their small size and quickness.
 
Elf - "forest casting"  This is an AUTOMATIC skill that allows the elf to have
a much faster casting rate while in a forested area.
 
Giant - "Crush" SYNTAX: crush <victim>
This is a combat-initiating attack that does large amounts of damage, and has
a chance of knocking the victim out, into the next room, or both.
 
Duergar - "critical strike" This is an AUTOMATIC skill.  Due to the duergar's
knowledge of dirty tactics, they can strike critical spots and deal more damage
to their victims when they do.
 
Merma - "dive"  SYNTAX: "dive" and "emerge"
While in the water, merma can dive to the bottom.  There, they cannot be attacked
unless the attacker is submerged as well.  To come back to the surface, the command
is "emerge"
 
Human - The human has no special abilities, but they may be any class and are not
vulnerable to anything.
 
Dwarf - "battle rage"  When a dwarf consumes any alcohol, the drunkeness allows them
to do much more damage.  However, you cannot quaff potions or eat while drunk, and
sometimes its really hard to walk when you're trashed.
 
